<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,564,1138,1164]" box="[189,564,1138,1164]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,564,1138,1164]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,564,1138,1164]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Distribution and conservation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1398,1186,1286]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
A narrow-range endemic (
<figureCitation box="[500,573,1186,1213]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[181,224,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[295,1278,1100,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[295,1278,1100,1891]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Distribution of narrow-range Afrodonta species. Af. geminodonta sp. nov. (purple triangles), Af. mystica sp. nov. (orange square), Af. pentodon sp. nov. (green circles) and Af. unilamellaris Connolly, 1933 (blue circle). Contour at 1000 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3762292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3762292/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), known only from the Mfongosi area (± 
<quantity box="[1070,1146,1186,1213]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
a.s.l.) in the Thukela River valley below Kranskop, 
<collectingRegion box="[568,756,1222,1248]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
; no accurate habitat data available. This area is not afforded any formal protection and is threatened by impacts related to subsistence agriculture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
